subtitle: When to get medical help
title: Warning signs
content:
Created by BabyCenter

Your body changes in many ways in pregnancy, and it is normal to wonder if you need to worry about any of these changes.

This is normal Are you tired one minute, fine the next, feeling nauseous in the mornings, getting indigestion, having to pass water more often, is your skin changing? feeling breathless? Welcome to pregnancy!

These are warning signs Go straight to the hospital if you have any of these feelings:

•	Pain in your belly

•	A high fever

•	A bad headache with blurred vision, and you are seeing spots in front of your eyes

•	Fluid leaking from your vagina

•	Pain when passing water

•	If you are past 5 months in your pregnancy, and your baby has stopped kicking or is kicking much less

•	If you are bleeding or have bleeding with pain.
